Package com.rb.nonbiz.json

Class RBJsonDoubleArray

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.json.RBJsonDoubleArray
public class RBJsonDoubleArray
extends java.lang.Object
JSON arrays don't have to have items of the same type in them. This class enforces that all items are doubles.

Classes in our system are normally immutable. JsonArray (a Google / 3rd party class, not ours) is not. The way we can make this class immutable is to return a new JsonArray every time we ask for one. Otherwise, if there were a JsonArray private member, a caller could retrieve it and add to it. This is less efficient, but safer.

Another advantage is that, once we know this can only hold doubles, we can have a test matcher that uses an epsilon.
